description:
This table `SectorCarrier` stores detailed information about radio access network sectors and their carriers, including configuration, performance, and operational status.

- `dateTime`: Timestamp of the data record.
- `Area_Name`: Name of the geographic area where the sector is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
- `CellId`: Unique identifier for the cell.
- `Id2`:  Duplicate of CellId.
- `Id3`:  An additional identifier, likely related to sector or carrier.
- `vsDataType`: Specifies the data type as 'vsDataSectorCarrier'.
- `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of the data format (e.g., EricssonSpecificAttributes).
- `SectorCarrier.noOfTxAntennas`: Number of configured transmit antennas.
- `SectorCarrier.noOfUsedTxAntennas`: Number of transmit antennas currently in use.
- `SectorCarrier.sectorCarrierType`: Type of sector carrier (e.g., NORMAL_SECTOR).
- `SectorCarrier.sectorShape`: Shape of the sector coverage area (e.g., HOTSPOT, MACRO).
- `SectorCarrier.essScLocalId`: Local identifier within the Ericsson system.
- `SectorCarrier.maxAllowedEirpPsd`: Maximum allowed Effective Isotropic Radiated Power (EIRP) power spectral density.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary8`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.rfBranchTxRef`: Reference to the transmit RF branch.
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigLevelThresh`: Threshold for Power Improvement Mitigation (PIM) level.
- `SectorCarrier.sectorFunctionRef`: Reference to the sector function within the network.
- `SectorCarrier.txPowerPersistentLock`: Indicates whether transmit power is persistently locked.
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigDlMutingFixed`: Indicates whether PIM mitigation downlink muting is fixed.
- `SectorCarrier.prsEnabled`: Status of Power Reduction Scheme (PRS) enablement.
- `SectorCarrier.availabilityStatus`: Availability status of the sector carrier.
- `SectorCarrier.rfBranchRxRef`: Reference to the receive RF branch.
- `SectorCarrier.usedSectorShape`:  Used sector shape.
- `SectorCarrier.virtualComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude`: Amplitude of virtual common channel beamforming weights.
- `SectorCarrier.essScPairId`: Pair identifier within the Ericsson system.
- `SectorCarrier.radioTransmitPerfMode`: Radio transmit performance mode (e.g., CAPACITY_GREEN).
- `SectorCarrier.virtualSector`:  Indicates if this is a virtual sector.
- `SectorCarrier.configuredMaxTxPower`: Configured maximum transmit power.
- `SectorCarrier.antCalModeTddAasDl`: Antenna calibration mode for TDD AAS downlink.
- `SectorCarrier.maximumTransmissionPower`: Maximum transmission power.
- `SectorCarrier.noOfUsedRxAntennas`: Number of receive antennas currently in use.
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigLevel`: Level of PIM mitigation.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary1`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary2`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigMinIntPwrAutoConfig`: Automatic configuration of minimum interference power for PIM mitigation.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary4`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary5`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.zzzTemporary6`: Placeholder for future use.
- `SectorCarrier.sectorCarrierId`: Unique identifier for the sector carrier.
- `SectorCarrier.reservedBy`:  Indicates what entity has reserved this resource.
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigDlMutingPeriod`: Period for PIM mitigation downlink muting.
- `SectorCarrier.noOfRxAntennas`: Number of configured receive antennas.
- `SectorCarrier.ulForcedTimingAdvanceCommand`: Forced uplink timing advance command.
- `SectorCarrier.beamOverlapEirpControl`: Control of EIRP for beam overlap.
- `SectorCarrier.virtualComChBeamfrmWtsPhase`: Phase of virtual common channel beamforming weights.
- `SectorCarrier.operationalState`: Operational state of the sector carrier (e.g., ENABLED).
- `SectorCarrier.pimMitigDlMutingPerc`: Percentage for PIM mitigation downlink muting.
- `SectorCarrier.verticalTaperType`: Type of vertical tapering used.
- `SectorCarrier.digitalTilt`: Digital tilt angle.
- `SectorCarrier.microSleepTxEnabled`: Status of micro-sleep transmit enablement.
